ABOUT

    This directory contains tinyramfs, the tool used to create a Linux boot
    image (initramfs).

    This is a fork of illilliti's tinyramfs. Original sources can be downloaded
    from: https://github.com/illiliti/tinyramfs.

FEATURES

    * No "local"s, no bashisms, only POSIX shell
    * Portable, no distro specific
    * Easy to use configuration
    * Build time and init time hooks
    * LUKS (detached header, key, password), LVM
    * mdev, mdevd, eudev, systemd-udevd

DEPENDENCIES

    * POSIX make (build time)
    * POSIX utilities
    * POSIX shell
    * switch_root(8)
    * mount(8)
    * cpio(1)
    * ldd(1) (optional, required for copying binary dependencies)
    * strip(1p) (optional, required for reducing image size by stripping
      binaries)
    * blkid(8) (optional, required for UUID, LABEL, PARTUUID support)
    * mdev OR mdevd OR eudev OR systemd-udevd OR CONFIG_UEVENT_HELPER (optional,
      required for modular kernel, /dev/mapper/* and /dev/disk/*)
    * lvm(8) (optional, required for LVM support)
    * cryptsetup(8) (optional, required for LUKS support)
    * busybox' loadkmap (optional, required for keymap support)
    * kmod OR busybox' modutils with patches/modprobe-kernel-version.patch (not
      required for monolithic kernel)

USAGE

    * Read tinyramfs.config(5) manual page and setup /etc/tinyramfs/config.
    * Next, run as root:
      $ tinyramfs -o "/boot/initramfs-$(uname -r)"
    * Update your bootloader (i.e. grub):
      $ grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg
    * Reboot.

THANKS

    * E5ten <https://github.com/E5ten>
    * dylanaraps <https://github.com/dylanaraps>

